author: Buzz Carrick
title: FC Dallas 2015 MLS Cup Playoff schedule
text:
By virtue of their Western Conference title, FC Dallas is the #1 seed in the Western Conference bracket of the 2015 Audi MLS Cup Playoffs.
After a bye in the Knockout Round (single game eliminator), FC Dallas (17-10-6, 57 points) will play the lowest remaining seed from the Knockout Round in a the Western Conference Semifinals (2 game home/away series) on Sunday, Nov. 1 (away) and Sunday, Nov. 8 (at Toyota Stadium).
If FC Dallas Should advance the Western Conference Finals (again home/away) will take place November 22nd (away) and 29th (Toyota Stadium). MLS Cup is December 6th.
Tickets to the first FC Dallas playoff matches, presented by Toyota, are on sale now in two-match packs, starting at $44. Fans that purchase before Friday, Oct. 23, will also receive a ticket for FC Dallas' regular season finale this Sunday, Oct. 25, for free. For more information visit fcdallas.com/playoffs .
FC Dallas Playoff Schedule * presented by Toyota *
Western Conference Semifinal Leg 1 [Away leg] - Sunday, November 1 st
Western Conference Semifinal Leg 2 [Home leg] - Sunday, November 8 th
Western Conference Final Leg 1 [Away leg] - Sunday, November 22 nd\
Western Conference Final Leg 2 [Home leg] - Sunday, November 29 th
MLS Cup - Sunday, December 6 th
Times and opponents are TBD On Twitter:
